<item>
            <title>[MSHADE-396] Improve SourceContent Shading</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MSHADE-396</link>
                <project id="12317921" key="MSHADE">Maven Shade Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MSHADE-252&quot; title=&quot;shadeSourcesContent is broken when combined with partial relocation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MSHADE-252&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MSHADE-252&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has greatly improved the shading of the source content. I used this version but found some problems in combination with a small pattern.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Examples:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should exclude replacement in the following situations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pattern: &quot;io&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
 Content: java.io.IOException;&lt;br/&gt;
 Content: private String myException;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pattern: io&lt;br/&gt;
 Content: private String ioInput&lt;br/&gt;
 Content: String io, val;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
