                            <comment id="17373493" author="reamer" created="Fri, 2 Jul 2021 12:44:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kriegaex&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kriegaex&quot;&gt;kriegaex&lt;/a&gt; it would be nice if you could check my PR, because you have made the last changes in this direction. it would be nice, if you could review my PR.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17373880" author="kriegaex" created="Sat, 3 Jul 2021 02:51:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Reamer&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Reamer&quot;&gt;Reamer&lt;/a&gt;, thanks for the notification. I am going to take a look as soon as I have some free cycles. Not being a committer in this project, my review is not authoritative, though. BTW, I am happy that someone uses my source shading implementation. It was heuristic to begin with - a perfect solution would require full Java parsing and probably some kind of source AST representation - and certainly has room for incremental improvement. This is the beauty of OSS development: There is always someone out there who can take your work one step further or sometimes even lift it to a whole new level. &#128578;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
